"sysstat" is a set of performance monitoring tools for Linux.
The package is designed to display how much processor time,
how many context switches and how much memory is used,
at a fine-grained level.

The "sar" command is used to display and schedule the collection of
system activity data.

The "iostat" command is used to display and control the
collection of statistics on I/O devices.

